<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <meta name="description" content="Web Accessibility Statement for [Company Name] — outlining our commitment to WCAG 2.1 and 2.2 Level AA conformance under the RPwD Act, 2016." />
  <title>[Company Name] – Web Accessibility Statement</title>
  <style>
    @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Sans:ital,opsz,wght@0,9..40,300;0,9..40,400;0,9..40,500;0,9..40,600&display=swap');

    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

    :root {
      --navy:         #0f1e3c;
      --ink:          #1e2535;
      --mid:          #4a5568;
      --soft:         #718096;
      --border:       #e2e8f0;
      --bg:           #f8fafc;
      --white:        #ffffff;
      --green:        #276749;
      --green-light:  #f0fff4;
      --amber:        #744210;
      --amber-light:  #fffbeb;
    }

    /* ─── Base ─── */
    body {
      font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
      background: var(--bg);
      color: var(--ink);
      line-height: 1.75;
      font-size: 16px;
    }

    /* Skip link for keyboard / screen reader users */
    .skip-link {
      position: absolute;
      top: -100%;
      left: 0;
      background: var(--navy);
      color: var(--white);
      padding: 10px 18px;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      text-decoration: none;
      z-index: 9999;
      border-radius: 0 0 6px 0;
    }
    .skip-link:focus { top: 0; }

    /* ─── Header ─── */
    header {
      background: var(--white);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      padding: 22px 0;
    }
    .header-inner {
      max-width: 820px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 0 32px;
    }
    .company-name {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--navy);
    }

    /* ─── Hero ─── */
    .hero {
      background: var(--navy);
      color: var(--white);
      padding: 64px 32px 56px;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .hero h1 {
      font-size: 1.85rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      line-height: 1.3;
      margin-bottom: 0;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    }
    .status-badge {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 8px;
      background: var(--amber-light);
      color: var(--amber);
      border: 1px solid #f6e05e;
      border-radius: 100px;
      padding: 6px 16px;
      font-size: 0.73rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      margin-top: 26px;
    }
    .status-badge::before {
      content: '';
      display: inline-block;
      width: 7px; height: 7px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      background: #d69e2e;
      flex-shrink: 0;
    }

    /* ─── Main ─── */
    main {
      max-width: 820px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 56px 32px 80px;
    }
    section { margin-bottom: 52px; }

    h2 {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--navy);
      margin-bottom: 16px;
      padding-bottom: 10px;
      border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border);
    }

    p {
      color: var(--mid);
      margin-bottom: 14px;
      font-size: 0.97rem;
    }

    strong { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 600; }

    a {
      color: #3182ce;
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-underline-offset: 2px;
    }
    a:hover, a:focus { color: #2b6cb0; outline: 2px solid #3182ce; outline-offset: 2px; border-radius: 2px; }

    ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0 0 14px; }
    ul li {
      position: relative;
      padding: 5px 0 5px 22px;
      color: var(--mid);
      font-size: 0.97rem;
    }
    ul li::before {
      content: '—';
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      color: var(--soft);
      font-size: 0.82rem;
      line-height: 1.9;
      aria-hidden: true;
    }

    /* ─── Callout boxes ─── */
    .info-box {
      background: var(--green-light);
      border-left: 4px solid #38a169;
      border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
      padding: 18px 22px;
      margin: 20px 0;
    }
    .info-box p { color: var(--green); margin: 0; }

    .notice-box {
      background: var(--amber-light);
      border-left: 4px solid #d69e2e;
      border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
      padding: 18px 22px;
      margin: 20px 0;
    }
    .notice-box p { color: var(--amber); margin: 0; }

    /* ─── Contact grid ─── */
    .contact-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(210px, 1fr));
      gap: 14px;
      margin-top: 20px;
    }
    .contact-card {
      background: var(--white);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 18px 20px;
    }
    .contact-card .label {
      font-size: 0.7rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--soft);
      margin-bottom: 6px;
    }
    .contact-card .value {
      font-size: 0.92rem;
      color: var(--navy);
      font-weight: 500;
      word-break: break-word;
    }

    /* ─── Footer ─── */
    footer {
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
      background: var(--white);
      padding: 40px 32px;
    }
    .footer-inner { max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; }
    .footer-label {
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--soft);
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }
    .footer-logos {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 36px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }
    .footer-logos img {
      height: 36px;
      width: auto;
      display: block;
    }
    .footer-logo-pivotal {
      display: block;
      height: 36px;
      width: auto;
    }
    .footer-logo-pivotal svg {
      height: 36px;
      width: auto;
      display: block;
    }
    .divider {
      width: 1px;
      height: 34px;
      background: var(--border);
      flex-shrink: 0;
    }
    .footer-copy {
      margin-top: 26px;
      font-size: 0.76rem;
      color: var(--soft);
    }

    @media (max-width: 600px) {
      .hero h1 { font-size: 1.4rem; }
      main { padding: 36px 20px 60px; }
      footer { padding: 32px 20px; }
      .footer-logos { gap: 24px; }
    }

    /* ─── Focus visible for all interactive elements ─── */
    :focus-visible {
      outline: 2px solid #3182ce;
      outline-offset: 3px;
      border-radius: 2px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <!-- Skip navigation for keyboard users -->
  <a class="skip-link" href="#main-content">Skip to main content</a>

  <header role="banner">
    <div class="header-inner">
      <span class="company-name" aria-label="Company name">[Company Name]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="hero" role="region" aria-label="Page title">
    <h1>[Company Name] – Web Accessibility Statement</h1>
    <div class="status-badge" aria-label="Status: Accessibility in progress">Accessibility in progress</div>
  </div>

  <main id="main-content">

    <section aria-labelledby="about-heading">
      <h2 id="about-heading">About This Statement</h2>
      <p>This accessibility statement applies to <strong>[Platform / Website Name]</strong>, operated by <strong>[Company Name]</strong>. We believe in equal access for all users and are actively working to bring our platform into full conformance with recognised accessibility standards.</p>
      <p>We have engaged <strong>Pivotal Accessibility</strong>, a DEPwD empaneled auditor, to conduct a formal audit of our platform. Based on this audit, we are implementing remediation measures in a phased approach.</p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="conformance-heading">
      <h2 id="conformance-heading">Conformance Status</h2>
      <p>The <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/standards-guidelines/wcag/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG)</a> define requirements for accessibility across three levels: Level A, Level AA and Level AAA.</p>
      <div class="notice-box" role="note">
        <p><strong>[Company Name]'s platform is currently partially conformant with WCAG 2.1 &amp; 2.2 Level AA in accordance with the Rights of Persons with Disabilities (RPwD) Act, 2016.</strong> This means some parts of the content do not yet fully meet the standard. We are actively remediating identified gaps and working toward full conformance.</p>
      </div>
      <p>An ACR (Accessibility Conformance Report) based on a VPAT (Voluntary Product Accessibility Template) will be made available for download once full conformance is achieved.</p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="measures-heading">
      <h2 id="measures-heading">Measures to Support Accessibility</h2>
      <p>[Company Name] has taken the following steps to address accessibility on our platform:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Commissioned a formal accessibility audit with Pivotal Accessibility, an external DEPwD-empaneled accessibility auditor</li>
        <li>Established an internal accessibility remediation roadmap based on audit findings</li>
        <li>Assigned ownership of accessibility improvements to our product and engineering teams</li>
        <li>Committed to reviewing accessibility as part of our ongoing release process</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="info-box" role="note">
        <p>Our audit was conducted in accordance with WCAG 2.1 &amp; 2.2 Level AA criteria and covers key user workflows on the platform.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="limitations-heading">
      <h2 id="limitations-heading">Known Limitations</h2>
      <p>While we are working toward full conformance, some parts of our platform may not yet fully meet WCAG 2.1 &amp; 2.2 Level AA requirements. We are actively identifying and remediating these gaps as part of an ongoing improvement process.</p>
      <p>Additionally, there might be certain sections or areas on the platform that are not owned by <strong>[Company Name]</strong>, controlled by a third party and might have accessibility barriers. We are working towards having the accessibility of these items enhanced, or finding a more accessible alternative for the same.</p>
      <p>If you encounter an accessibility barrier, please let us know via the feedback mechanism below and we will do our best to address it promptly.</p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="feedback-heading">
      <h2 id="feedback-heading">Feedback &amp; Contact</h2>
      <p>We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of our platform. If you experience any barriers, or require alternate and reasonable accommodations, please reach out — we aim to respond within 2 business days.</p>
      <div class="contact-grid">
        <div class="contact-card">
          <div class="label" id="email-label">Email</div>
          <div class="value" aria-labelledby="email-label">
            <a href="mailto:[accessibility@yourcompany.com]">[accessibility@yourcompany.com]</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="contact-card">
          <div class="label" id="phone-label">Phone</div>
          <div class="value" aria-labelledby="phone-label">[+91-XXXXXXXXXX]</div>
        </div>
        <div class="contact-card">
          <div class="label" id="address-label">Postal Address</div>
          <div class="value" aria-labelledby="address-label">[Company registered address]</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p style="margin-top:16px;">This statement was last updated on <strong>[Month Year]</strong>.</p>
    </section>

  </main>

